trend_summary: Over the sequence, wooded parcels gradually gave way to curvilinear subdivisions and roadside commercial clusters. Infill and edge expansion raised impervious cover, yet sizeable forest patches persist. Road corridors were widened, improving regional connectivity. Overall, the area evolved from lightly settled woodland to a more continuous suburban mosaic of houses, strip malls and light-industrial lots.
notable_changes: Forest blocks in the northwest and south cleared for new residential subdivisions.
Expansion of a light-industrial/commercial park along the northeastern arterial.
Widening and straightening of the main east-west highway, with added junctions.
Progressive increase in impervious surfaces and thinning backyard tree canopy.
